---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is OH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points"
  description="OH is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (O=1, H=4). An exclamation of surprise. Extensions: OHO, OHS. Free word checker."
  keywords="is oh a scrabble word, oh scrabble, oh valid word, oh points scrabble, two letter words with h, oho ohs scrabble, oh definition"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is OH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points",
    "description": "OH is a valid Scrabble word in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 5 points (O=1, H=4). An exclamation of surprise.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-oh-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is OH a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! OH is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (international) dictionaries. It scores 5 points (O=1, H=4) and is an exclamation expressing surprise, wonder, or understanding. It's one of the most versatile 2-letter H words." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What words extend from OH in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OH extends into OHO (6pts, an exclamation of surprise), OHS (6pts, plural). It also accepts front hooks: BOH, DOH, FOH, NOH, OOH, POH, SOH. These give you multiple ways to score from an existing OH on the board." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the difference between OH, AH, and UH in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "All three score 5 points and are valid in both dictionaries. OH expresses surprise, AH expresses realization, and UH expresses hesitation. Strategically they're equivalent — all let you place H for 4 points via a 2-letter word. The choice depends on which vowel (O, A, or U) is available on the board or your rack." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Checker</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is OH a Scrabble Word? — Yes, Valid for 5 Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Green Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">OH — 5 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">O=1, H=4 · Valid in TWL ✓ · Valid in SOWPODS ✓</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An exclamation of surprise or wonder. One of the most common 2-letter words in everyday English and an essential H-placement tool in competitive Scrabble.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">H=4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Key Tile</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">OHO, OHS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dictionaries</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Definition & Usage</h2>
      <p>OH is an interjection expressing surprise ("oh, I didn't expect that!"), understanding ("oh, now I get it"), or wonder. As a noun, it can also mean the exclamation itself or a zero (as in phone numbers). The plural OHS is valid.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📖 Dictionary Entry</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-medium">OH</span> (interjection/noun) — used to express surprise, pain, annoyance, or understanding. Also used to address someone: "Oh, John!" Plural: <span class="text-white font-medium">OHS</span>. Extended form: <span class="text-white font-medium">OHO</span> (expressing triumphant surprise).</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Extensions & Hooks</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OHO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OHS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OOH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOH</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OH vs AH vs UH:</span> All score 5 points. Choose based on which vowel is available. If O is on the board next to a premium square, play OH. If A is there, play AH. Flexibility is key — know all three.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OHO for the hook:</span> OH extends to OHO (6pts) by adding O at the end. This is useful when OH is already on the board — you score OHO plus any crossword from the new O touching adjacent tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel scoring:</span> OH parallel to an existing word scores both the OH and every crossword letter it touches. A well-placed parallel OH can net 15-20 points from just two tiles.</p></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ OH, AH, UH, EH</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">All 5pts — vowel + H pattern. Valid in both dictionaries. Essential for H placement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ HM = 7pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest 2-letter H word. No vowel needed. Valid TWL + SOWPODS. Use when no vowel is available.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ah-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AH a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-uh-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is UH a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble word checker, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
